Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.21,0:00:03.66,Default,Lain,0,0,0,,Mom said that she went to my school to ask for a leave of absence.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.20,0:00:08.55,Default,Lain,0,0,0,,I thought that I ought to feel glad that I won’t have to go to school, but I’m sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.20,0:00:11.66,Default,Lain,0,0,0,,I’ve genuinely been separated from society.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.32,0:00:14.99,Default,Lain,0,0,0,,I feel that I’ve been rejected by everyone, and I’m sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.85,0:00:18.15,Default,Lain,0,0,0,,Can't I live an ordinary life anymore?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.85,0:00:23.38,Default,Lain,0,0,0,,Dad won’t come home and Mom looks worn out.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.18,0:00:26.27,Default,Lain,0,0,0,,Why won’t Dad come home?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.97,0:00:29.10,Default,Lain,0,0,0,,Doesn’t he want to see me anymore?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.85,0:00:32.12,Default,Lain,0,0,0,,Doesn’t Dad like me anymore?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.76,0:00:34.12,Default,Lain,0,0,0,,I want to see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.66,0:00:39.14,Default,Lain,0,0,0,,I fell asleep weeping, and saw hallucinations again.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.62,0:00:40.43,Default,Lain,0,0,0,,It’s scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.89,0:00:42.78,Default,Lain,0,0,0,,I can see them whether I’m asleep or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.35,0:00:45.39,Default,Lain,0,0,0,,I can’t believe it myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.39,0:00:46.54,Default,Lain,0,0,0,,I don’t understand it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.14,0:00:51.50,Default,Lain,0,0,0,,I want someone to prove to me that I am the person that I know I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.11,0:00:53.56,Default,Lain,0,0,0,,I want to see Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.93,0:00:55.64,Default,Lain,0,0,0,,I want to see Dad and hug him.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.15,0:00:57.55,Default,Lain,0,0,0,,As he tells me that everything will be fine.
